article.headline: East Tennessee State 73, Milligan 47
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Courtney Pigram led ETSU with 23 points in a 73-47 win over Milligan Saturday night. The Buccaneers were also helped by freshman Mike Smith with a career-high 20 points and six rebounds and Eryk Thomas with 11 points and eight rebounds. The Buccaneer's defense held Milligan to just 16 percent shooting in the first half and ETSU led Milligan 41-15 at intermission. Milligan improved in the second half, matching ETSU 32-32, but never caught up. Zach Dezarn led Milligan with 10 points and four rebounds. ETSU shot 47 percent from the field and 42-percent from the 3-point range, hitting 11 3-pointers, a season high.
